==English==
===Verb phrase===
'''to do a...''' ('''doing a...''', '''did a...''') [followed by a [[name]]]
#to [[emulate]] a behavior generally attributed to the individual named
#*''He '''''did a Henry VIII''''' and got married six times.''
===Usage note===
Can either refer to the actions of a famous person, real or fictitious, that would be understood by most anyone, or to the actions of an individual known mainly by the speaker and his audience.
